# 6. 優しい思い出と現実

Kanade: That was the first song I ever composed.
Kanade: After that, I started composing more songs while receiving advice from my dad.
Kanade: Like what kind of songs would make both my parents smile...
Kanade: And what would make them feel happy... I wanted to compose those kinds of songs.
Rin: I see...
Rin: You must really love your mom and dad...
Kanade: I do...
Kanade: My mom always knew how to make me feel better... If I ever felt scared or worried she'd give me a hug, and she always sang lullabies to me whenever it was bedtime...
Kanade: My dad was also really nice... He always praised me and gave me pats on the head.
Kanade: Whenever we were all together, everything felt so warm and happy.
Kanade: They'd always smile whenever I composed a new song...
Kanade: Which always puts a smile on my face...
Rin: That's really nice...
Kanade: Huh?
Rin: I understand now that music means everything to you, Kanade.
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Yes, it does...
Kanade: (Music was always a part of our lives in some way... And that's what made us happy.)
Kanade: (Which is why I love music so much...)
Kanade: (But...)
Kanade: (Because of me, Dad...)
Kanade: (He...)
Rin: Kanade...?
Kanade: Oh...
Rin: Is something wrong? You don't look so good.
Kanade: I should head back... I need to finish working on that song.
Kanade: (Because my goal is still to compose songs that can save people...)
Kanade: (For as long as I can...)
Rin: But...
Kanade: I'm okay, and I'm sorry for making you worry...
Kanade: Thank you for listening. I feel a little better now.
Kanade: I'll come back once our song's finished...
Rin: Kanade...
Rin: Okay...
KAITO: ...
KAITO: Interesting...
KAITO: (I didn't know that's why she's composing these songs.)
KAITO: (Which is likely striking a chord with Mafuyu.)
KAITO: (And yet...)
KAITO: She clearly tried to suppress whatever she was feeling just now...
